content.description: The middle of the face that beckons to be climbed. Was going to be Tales From Gnarnia, but the approach and landing of this problem makes the name more valid. Anyways, climb the middle of the face starting just left of perth and use all sorts of sharp, painful crimps. I would ask that any future ascents be mindful that the lichen on this boulder make it VERY cool. Please try to not scrape too much off. The view from the top is SPECTACULAR and if the movement was little better, it would be 4 stars no doubt.
content.protection: The more pads the better. Landing is super hairy.
content.location: Start in the middle of the Australia Boulder. Climb up. Don't fall. Easy to walk off.
North arete of the Australia boulder, left side of face, ends around the corner a bit.

content.description: Good V2 with an interesting start and landing!
content.location:
Right side of the Australia Boulder located in the North East Bluff talus field. The boulder faces away from the bluff trail and is only about 20 yards from it. 

  Start with your left hand in a good in-cut of a right-slating crack.

content.description: A few steps from the East Bluff trail, out in the upper part of the Monolith Talus boulder field.
